{
  "text": "In this paper, we introduce the notion of an embedded graph grammar which extends the graph grammar model [CITATION_1] from a purely topological construct to one that includes geometry, continuous dynamics and local conditions on the evolution of those dynamics. We present this model through an example that also highlights a hierarchical and systemsoriented approach to using graph and embedded graph grammars. Methods such as the composition of grammars, structured labeling and lexicographic ordering of Lyapunov functions on grammars allow us to design grammars in a principled manner.",
